-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- Real-Data HDF5 Ingestion Showcase: Handwritten Digit Classification
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- Uses the real UCI Machine Learning Repository "Optical Recognition of
-- Handwritten Digits" dataset (Alpaydin & Kaynak, 1998): 8x8 grayscale
-- bitmaps of handwritten digits 0-9, pixel intensities 0-16. Downloaded
-- from https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/machine-learning-databases/optdigits/
-- via `cargo run --example gen_digits_data` -- genuinely external data,
-- not synthetic (unlike examples/pbmc_cell_typing.lnl, the first showcase
-- built this session).
--
-- This example specifically targets the scientific-connector ingestion
-- path (HDF5/Numpy/Zarr), which two real engine bugs were found and fixed
-- against while building it:
--   1. IMPORT DATASET FROM wrote a package LOAD DATASET could never load
--      back (missing legacy metadata sidecar) -- fixed in v0.1.55.
--   2. All three connectors flattened every N-D array to 1D, discarding
--      shape -- fixed in v0.1.56 (Arrow Field metadata side-channel).
--
-- examples/data/digits_centroids.h5 contains ONE real HDF5 dataset,
-- "centroids", of genuine shape (10, 64): row i is the empirical mean
-- pixel image (flattened 8x8 -> 64) for real digit class i, averaged over
-- ~370 real downloaded samples per class (the held-out query samples used
-- for classification below are never included in their own class's
-- average). Before v0.1.56, ingesting this file would have silently
-- produced one nonsensical Vector[640] -- all 640 numbers, from all 10
-- classes, flattened into a single "row" -- instead of 10 real Vector(64)
-- rows. Step 2 demonstrates the fixed behavior directly.

DROP DATABASE IF EXISTS hdf5_digit_classification
CREATE DATABASE hdf5_digit_classification
USE hdf5_digit_classification

-- ─── 1. IMPORT/LOAD round trip (v0.1.55 fix) ───────────────────────────────
-- Previously: IMPORT DATASET FROM reported success and wrote real files to
-- disk, but a subsequent LOAD DATASET always failed with "Dataset not
-- found" -- the legacy .meta.json sidecar LOAD DATASET requires was never
-- written by the IMPORT path. This now round-trips correctly (note the 640
-- rows below: IMPORT DATASET FROM uses the relational/Parquet path, which
-- is intentionally row-per-scalar -- 10 x 64 flattened -- and out of scope
-- for the shape-preservation fix demonstrated in step 2 next).

IMPORT DATASET FROM "examples/data/digits_centroids.h5" AS centroids_import
LOAD DATASET centroids_import
SHOW ALL DATASETS

-- ─── 2. Shape-preserving tensor ingestion (v0.1.56 fix) ────────────────────
-- USE DATASET FROM takes the tensor-first path. Before the fix, this real
-- (10, 64) array would have materialized as a single Vector[640] row. It
-- now correctly yields 10 rows, each a real Vector(64) -- one row per real
-- digit-class centroid.

USE DATASET FROM "examples/data/digits_centroids.h5" AS centroids
SHOW SCHEMA centroids
SHOW centroids

-- ─── 3. Real linear algebra directly on the ingested tensor ────────────────
-- centroids_centroids is the raw (10, 64) tensor USE DATASET FROM registers
-- (named "<dataset-name>_<hdf5-field-name>"). TRANSPOSE + MATMUL compute a
-- genuine 10x10 Gram matrix of dot products between every pair of real
-- digit-class centroids -- visually similar digit pairs (e.g. 4 and 9, or
-- 3 and 8) should show higher off-diagonal values than visually distinct
-- pairs (e.g. 0 and 1).

LET centroids_T = TRANSPOSE centroids_centroids
LET centroid_similarity = MATMUL centroids_centroids centroids_T
SHOW SHAPE centroid_similarity
SHOW centroid_similarity

-- ─── 4. Labeled reference table for classification ─────────────────────────
-- The same real centroid values as digits_centroids.h5 above (produced by
-- the same generator script), re-expressed as a labeled relational table.
-- The HDF5 tensor ingested in step 2 has no room for a class label, so
-- this mirrors pbmc_cell_typing.lnl's reference_profiles pattern to make
-- classification results reportable by digit class.

DATASET reference_centroids COLUMNS (
    digit_class: Int,
    centroid: Vector(64)
)

